        "intro": "If your parent is struggling with high heating bills in Alaska, they may qualify for free home weatherization services worth up to $4,000. This federal program provides insulation, furnace repairs, window sealing, and other energy efficiency improvements at no cost to reduce monthly utility bills.\n\nThe program prioritizes households with seniors 60+, disabled residents, or families with children under 6. Income limits are generous: $39,100 for a single person, $52,860 for a couple (2026). Both homeowners and renters qualify, and there are no asset limits.\n\nBecause services are delivered through regional providers across Alaska, you'll apply directly through your area's organization rather than a state office. The catch: homes that received weatherization in the last 15 years are ineligible, and there may be wait times since providers prioritize the most vulnerable households first.",
