        "intro": "If your parent qualifies for nursing home care but wants to remain at home, the MSSP Waiver provides comprehensive home and community services through Medi-Cal. This program assigns a care team (nurses and social workers) who coordinate all services — from personal care and adult day programs to home-delivered meals and emergency response systems.\n\nYour parent must be 60+, eligible for Medi-Cal, and need nursing facility level care (meaning they require daily help with activities like bathing, dressing, or medication management). Because this isn't an entitlement program, there are limited slots — 11,940 statewide for 2024-2029 — which means waitlists exist even if your parent qualifies.\n\nUnlike some programs that let you hire family members, MSSP requires using licensed agencies. The program covers the full cost of an individualized service plan designed to keep your parent safely at home.",
