        "intro": "If your parent is 60+ and struggling with grocery costs, CalFresh provides monthly food benefits on an EBT card. Because your parent is a senior, they get special advantages: no asset limits (they can keep their home, car, and retirement savings), extra deductions for medical expenses over $35/month including Medicare premiums, and the ability to buy prepared meals at participating restaurants statewide.\n\nBenefits start at $15/month for eligible seniors and scale up based on household size and expenses. Your parent can apply as a separate household even if living with family, and the income test is more generous for seniors — it's based on net income after deductions, not gross income.",
