        "intro": "If your parent is struggling with high heating and cooling bills, Colorado's Weatherization Assistance Program provides free energy-efficiency improvements installed by qualified technicians. This includes insulation, air sealing, weatherstripping, and other modifications tailored to your parent's specific home needs.\n\nQualifying households receive a professional energy assessment followed by customized improvements at no cost. Because services are determined by individual home assessment, the exact improvements vary but are designed to reduce energy costs long-term. Your parent automatically qualifies if they receive SNAP, LEAP, TANF, SSI, or other public assistance. Otherwise, income limits vary by county, household size, and utility provider — making this program complex but potentially valuable.",
