        "faqs": [
          {
            "question": "What if my parent can drive but has trouble cooking?",
            "answer": "They may still qualify. Programs assess overall ability to shop and prepare nutritious meals safely, not just transportation. Conditions like arthritis, vision problems, or balance issues that make cooking difficult often qualify even if your parent can still drive short distances."
          },
          {
            "question": "Can my parent get meals if their income is too high for the sliding scale?",
            "answer": "Yes. Unlike other programs, Meals on Wheels doesn't have strict income cutoffs. Higher-income participants pay the suggested donation (typically $3.50-$7.50 per meal), but no one is denied service for inability to pay."
          },
          {
            "question": "What happens if we move to a different county in Colorado?",
            "answer": "Your parent will need to reapply with the new county's provider. Each area has different rules, wait times, and delivery zones. Start the application process before moving to avoid gaps in service."
          },
          {
            "question": "How long can my parent receive meals?",
            "answer": "As long as they remain eligible and homebound. Some programs offer short-term service (minimum 5 days) after hospital discharge, while others provide ongoing daily delivery for years. Regular reassessments ensure continued need."
          },
          {
            "question": "What if there's no answer when the delivery person comes?",
            "answer": "Most programs have safety check procedures — if your parent doesn't answer, staff will call emergency contacts or local authorities for a wellness check. This daily contact provides peace of mind beyond just nutrition."
          },
          {
            "question": "Can my parent get weekend meals too?",
            "answer": "Some areas offer frozen weekend meals, but availability varies by provider. Ask specifically about weekend options when you call — it's not automatically included with weekday delivery."
          }
        ],
        "phone": "303-294-0111",
