        "intro": "If your parent is dealing with eviction threats, denied benefits, or other civil legal problems, Colorado Legal Services provides free attorney help for seniors 60 and older. This isn't just legal advice — they can represent your parent in court, help file cases, and handle everything from housing disputes to tax problems.\n\nBecause seniors 60+ get priority access, your parent may qualify even if their income is slightly above the usual poverty guidelines. Some offices like Larimer County have no income limits at all for seniors. The program covers civil matters only — housing, public benefits, consumer issues, and limited immigration help — but not criminal or traffic cases.",
