        "intro": "If your parent is 60+ and received a utility disconnection notice or has a past-due energy bill, they may qualify for emergency help paying electricity, gas, or propane bills. Because this program pays the utility company directly, your parent won't handle the money — it goes straight toward the overdue balance. This is crisis assistance, meaning your parent must already be behind on bills or facing shutoff to qualify.\n\nThe program is run county by county across Florida, so income limits and benefit amounts vary by location. Most counties use 150% of the Federal Poverty Level as the income limit, while some areas provide up to $400 per season (summer cooling or winter heating). Your parent automatically qualifies if they receive SNAP, TANF, or SSI benefits.",
