          {
            "question": "What if we live in a rural area where delivery might be difficult?",
            "answer": "Delivery zones vary by county and local provider. Some rural addresses may be outside delivery areas. When you call the Elder Helpline, they'll tell you if your parent's address is in the service area. Each county has different coverage areas and providers."
          },
          {
            "question": "How many meals will my parent receive per week?",
            "answer": "This varies significantly. If your parent has Medicaid long-term care, they may receive 5-10 meals per authorization period. Other participants might receive different amounts based on their assessment and local program capacity. The assessment will determine how many meals your parent needs and qualifies for."
          },
          {
            "question": "What if my parent has special dietary needs like diabetic or low-sodium meals?",
            "answer": "Many programs offer medically tailored meals, especially for participants with Medicaid coverage. During the assessment, provide detailed information about your parent's dietary restrictions, medical conditions, and any doctor's recommendations. This information helps determine both eligibility and the type of meals provided."
          },
          {
            "question": "Can my parent's spouse also receive meals?",
            "answer": "Possibly, but you need to verify this with your local program. Some programs serve spouses or other household members, while others serve only the qualified individual. Ask specifically about household members when you call for the assessment."
          }
