        "intro": "If your parent is 65+ and lives in an assisted living facility, adult family care home, or mental health residential treatment facility in Florida, they may qualify for monthly cash assistance to help cover facility costs. Optional State Supplementation (OSS) provides additional money when SSI benefits aren't enough to pay for care.\n\nThis program fills the gap between what your parent receives from SSI and what their facility charges. The state calculates the payment by taking the facility's provider rate, adding a personal needs allowance (like $54/month), then subtracting your parent's countable income. Income limit: $828.40/month for an individual in assisted living, $1,656.80/month for a married couple (current rates).\n\nOSS only applies to residents of licensed facilities — not independent living or home care. Your parent must need help with daily activities like bathing, dressing, or medication management, confirmed through medical evaluation.",
