        "intro": "If your parent is 55+ and needs nursing home-level care but wants to stay in their community, PACE provides all their medical care through one coordinated team. Because PACE covers all Medicare and Medicaid services under one program, your parent won't need to coordinate between separate doctors, specialists, or insurance plans — one interdisciplinary team manages everything from primary care to prescription drugs to transportation.\n\nUnlike most programs, PACE has no income or asset limits. Your parent qualifies based on clinical need (requiring nursing home-level care) and geography (living in a PACE service area). If your parent has both Medicare and Medicaid, all services come with no deductibles or copays. If they only have Medicare, they pay a monthly premium.\n\nPACE availability is extremely limited in Idaho. Your parent must live in a specific service area where a PACE organization operates, and these programs may have waitlists due to enrollment caps.",
