        "faqs": [
          {
            "question": "Can Mom keep her current doctors if she enrolls in PACE?",
            "answer": "No. PACE requires your mom to receive all medical care through their team of providers. She cannot see outside doctors or specialists unless PACE specifically approves and arranges it. This is a major change from traditional Medicare."
          },
          {
            "question": "What if Mom's income is too high for Medicaid but she can't afford private insurance?",
            "answer": "PACE offers a private pay option based on your mom's income and assets. The PACE provider will calculate her monthly premium during the enrollment process. Many families find this more affordable than coordinating multiple services separately."
          },
          {
            "question": "Can Mom keep her house if she qualifies for PACE?",
            "answer": "Yes. Your mom's primary home doesn't count toward Medicaid asset limits, regardless of value. PACE is designed to help people stay in their homes instead of moving to nursing facilities."
          },
          {
            "question": "What happens if Mom needs to move to a different area of Michigan?",
            "answer": "Each PACE provider serves exclusive geographic areas. If your mom moves outside her current PACE service area, she would need to disenroll and find new healthcare coverage. Check service boundaries before any moves."
          },
          {
            "question": "How is this different from other home care programs like MIChoice?",
            "answer": "PACE provides all medical care plus home support services through one program. MIChoice only covers home care services — you still need separate doctors and insurance. Your mom cannot be enrolled in both programs at the same time."
          },
          {
            "question": "What if there's a waiting list for PACE in our area?",
            "answer": "Waiting lists vary by provider and region. Contact your local PACE provider to ask about current wait times and get on their list. Continue your mom's current care while waiting, as PACE cannot guarantee enrollment timing."
          }
        ],
