        "intro": "If your parent needs nursing home level care but wants to stay at home, PACE provides everything under one roof — primary care, specialists, prescriptions, transportation, adult day programs, and home care services. Because all providers work as one team, your parent won't need to coordinate between separate doctors, and you won't need to manage multiple appointments and referrals.\n\nPACE is only available in select New Hampshire areas through Neighborhood Healthcare, which operates 3 centers. Your parent must be 55+ and need significant daily help with activities like bathing, dressing, or medication management (nursing facility level of care). Most participants qualify for both Medicare and Medicaid, but the program accepts private pay as well.\n\n95% of PACE participants live in the community rather than nursing homes, even with complex medical needs. The program includes 24/7 emergency access and covers services that traditional Medicare often doesn't, like extensive transportation and social support.",
