        "id": "south-dakota-hope-waiver",
        "name": "HOPE Waiver (Home & Community-Based Options and Person Centered Excellence)",
        "shortName": "HOPE Waiver",
        "tagline": "Get in-home care, respite services, and meals for your parent instead of nursing home placement — if they qualify for nursing facility level care.",
        "programType": "benefit",
        "complexity": "deep",
        "geographicScope": {
          "type": "state",
          "stateVariation": false
        },
        "intro": "If your parent needs daily help with bathing, dressing, or medication management but wants to stay home, South Dakota's HOPE Waiver can provide in-home care services, respite care, adult day programs, and meals. Because this waiver covers people who qualify for nursing facility level care, your parent must need significant daily assistance to be eligible.\n\nThe program serves people 65+ or adults with qualifying Social Security disabilities. Income limit: $2,901/month for single applicants (2025). Your parent can have up to $2,000 in countable assets. The program is capped at 1,834 people statewide, so availability varies.",
