        "intro": "If your parent is 55+ and at risk of nursing home placement, Virginia PACE may cover all their medical care through one coordinated team — allowing them to stay in their community. Because PACE becomes your parent's sole Medicare and Medicaid provider, they won't need to coordinate between different doctors, specialists, or facilities.\n\nPACE covers everything from primary care and prescription drugs to adult day care, physical therapy, and even nursing facility care if temporarily needed. Your parent must live in a PACE service area (not available statewide) and qualify medically for nursing facility level of care. Income limit: approximately $2,901/month for 2025. Asset limit: typically $2,000 (excluding home and one vehicle).\n\nOnly about 7% of PACE participants live in nursing facilities long-term — the program is designed to keep seniors in their communities with comprehensive support.",
