        "intro": "If your parent is 65+ and needs help paying for medical care or long-term care, Vermont's Medicaid for the Aged, Blind and Disabled (ABD) covers everything from doctor visits to nursing home care. This program is specifically for seniors, blind individuals, or people with disabilities who meet strict income and asset limits.\n\nUnlike regular health insurance, Medicaid ABD also covers long-term care services — both nursing home care and home-based care through Vermont's Choices for Care program. Your parent gets a care team that coordinates all services, from medical appointments to daily living assistance.\n\nIncome limits vary by location: $1,375/month for individuals living outside Chittenden County, and higher limits inside Chittenden County. Asset limits are $2,000 for a single person.",
